LAYER ONE DEVICES OF THE OSI MODEL..


Anolog modem : it is derived from the modilator /demodulator.

..> modem were develpoed to take the digital signals from the digital node convert it into the analog signal (this is called modulating ) which need to be placed on the wire. 
..> Even it would accept the analog signal from the wire and convert it to the digital signal that node can understand(this is demodulating)


..> Modems provide for a single connection to  network.

..> these only deals with the wires , and the wire is in the physical layer if the OSI model.



HUB: A hub functions as a concentrator/repeater in that it does not care about where the signal comes from or where it is going.



..>it takes the  electrical signal that come to it and sends that signal out to all other ports.

..>  A hub may have just a few ports , or it may have many ports.





++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++


LAYER TWO  DEVICES OF THE OSI MODEL..


Switch:   A Switch is a networking device. It connects multiple devices together on a single network and routes the information. 

...> A switch is used to send the data packets to a particular network by using the mac address over the network.



...> a switch will only communicates with the local network devices.



...> A switch works on the data link layer of the osi model.




BRIDGE :

Wireless Access Point(WAP): A wap is a specific type of the network bridge that connects wireless netork segments with the wired network segments .


..> a wap will only communicates with the local network devices.







++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++


LAYER THREE   DEVICES OF THE OSI MODEL..



Multilayer layer switch(MLS): it provides the normal layer two services but it will also provides layer 3 or higher OSI model services.



...> MLS is a highly programmable and comple network device .

...> this allow devices to communicate and pass data to a non local network devices.




Router: It is a common networking decive for connecting diff networks together .


..> A router is a gateway that passes data between one or more local area networks (LANs). Routers use the Internet Protocol (IP) to send IP packets containing data and IP addresses of sending and destination devices located on separate local area networks.



++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++


SECURITY DEVICES.


Fire wall: it blocks packets from entering or leaving the network.

..>a fire wall can be placed on the routers or hosts,


...> it functions at the multiple layers of the OSi model

..> layers at 2,3,4,7


..> vIa stateless inspection : the fire wall will examine every packet against a set of rules , once the packet matches a rule, the rule is enforced , and the specified action is taken.



via stateful inspection:
the fire wall only examine the state of the connection between networks.
it acts as the ffirst line if defence in protecting the internal network from outside threats.






Intrusion detection system (IDS): it is a passive  system designed to identify when a network is breached and when attack against the network is occuring.



an ids cannot prevent or stop a breach or attack on its own.
it receives a copy of all traffic and evaluates it against a set of standards.




Intrusion prevention system(IPS) :it is an active system designed to stop a breach or attack from damaging the network.

..>it is programmed to make an cative response to the situation.

..>it is placed in between a router with the firewall.


..>it will inform to the network administrator through the use of logs files, sms, notification system



Virtual private network: 







IP: Internet protocol 
 ..>the protocol are the set of rules .

Dynamic ip: These are the temporary ip's which is provided by the ISP(internet service provider)

static ip's: These are the permanent, which can not be chanaged. ip's. which is purchsed by the large compnnies.



MAC media access control:

..>each device has the its own mac address

..>it is the physical address of the device

..>working: when we connceted to the d-link router , and we request an file from the internet then the request is send to the server and come to the router , then this wifi-router will search for the particular mac address from which the request is come , because for our router many devices are connected, it will become difficult if mac address is not there.


 

MAC Spoofing: 

A MAC spoofing attack consists of changing the MAC address of a network device (network card). As a result, an attacker can redirect data sent to a device to another device and gain access to this data.




server:
..> a server is a software or hardware device that accepts and responds to reuests made over a network.

client:

..>the device that makes , the request, and recevies a responce from the server is called client.


_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
 

TOPOLOGIES:Network topology is the arrangement or connection of the various  of the elements/nodes through lines/wires of a communication network.
 


BUS TOPOLOGIES:

It is a computer network where every computer/node is connected to a single main cable.


...less cost 
... if that main cable is not working then entire system will not work.
... it reqired a lot of cabling.
...security is very low 

MESH TOPOLOGIES:

it is a computer network where every computer/node is connected to another via dedicated channels/wires.

...communication is very fast
...more security.
...required a lot of cables/wires.
... more maintenance is high.

STAR TOPOLOGIES :

it is a computer network where every computer/nodes are connected to a  centrall single hub through cables.


...communication is fast 
...easy to identify the faults
...cost of installation is high.
...if hub is not working then entire system will not work

RING TOPOLOGIES :


It is a computer network where every computers/nodes are connected in the ring(closed )form.

...the data flows in one direction only 
...less cost 
...the data is fastly transferd
...less secure
.. .if one node is not working then entire system will not work. 


TREE TOPOLOGIES :
This topology is the variation of the Star topology.
... it has the many hubs




HYBRID TOPTOLOGIES : 

This topological technology is the combination of all the various types of topologies .


...topology is very flexible.
...The size of the network can be easily expanded by adding new devices.
... challenging to design the architecture of the Hybrid Networ

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

OSI model :

open system interconnection:

..> It's describes how devices send, receive data.





Benefits of osi:
..>divides the network communication process into layers to be easier to troubleshoot.
..> layer separetion makes changes in one layer do not affect other layers.

..> layers can interact with each other




application layer :
..>In this layer  the user will interact with the web browser and

..> in this layer the user will request the web browser to return the content in the required format.And the web browser will sent the requested content to the application layer.

presentation layer:

..> after receiving the data from the application layer here the data is compressed/decompressed.

..>and here the data isencrypted/ decrypted 

Session layer:



..> in this layer estab of the session, managing of the session, controlling of the session, terminating of the session will happen for the communucation

..> a session is estb for the communication purpose 


Transport layer:


Here in the transport layer , by using proper protocols only the reliable messages will be transmitted
..>here the data will be organized  into proper segments.

..>here data is transported in the order way.

..> if data will duplicated, then it is properly remove it and segment it.

..> it ensures that messages are delivered error-free, in sequence , with no loss.

..>by the acknowledment it will ensure whether data is sended or not and recevied or not.

..> estab two way connection between the nodes before data transmission.


NETWORK LAYER:

..> in this layer the data is organised in to the data packets.

..>the router works in the network layer

..> selects the best path for moving towards the destination

...> here it receive the segments of data from transport layer and converts them to packets by adding logical addressing information (source, destination address).

DATA LINK layer:


..>here in this layer we have the logical link between the nodes.

..> here the data will be organized/converted  into the frames.

..>  here the frames will be error free

..>here Mac address of the devices is present 

..>these frames has the data packages and the sender/receiver physical addresses.

..>switches and bridges devices work in the data link layer.


PHYSICAL LAYER:


..>Here in the physical layer bits are transmited into the /wires, guided medium and unguided medium cables.


...> Hub, repeater work in the physical layer.



________________________________________________________________________________________


Basically in every  device many applications/services running. 

ip addresss identifies the system .
port number identifies the application on the system .




ip address : it is a logical address used to identify a device on the network.I t is provided by the ISP. Any device connected to the internet is assigned a unique IP address for identification. 

port number :port numbers identify particular applications or services on a system. 

socket address: ip address+ port number


