Computer Network Architecture
_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________


Computer Network Architecture is nothing but how computers are organized and how tasks are allocated to the computer.

types of the architecture:

i) peer-to-peer network.
ii) client/server network.


peer-to-peer network:

Peer-To-Peer network is a network in which all the computers are linked together with equal privilege and responsibilities for processing the data.


client/server network: 

Client/Server network is a network model designed for the end users called clients, to access the resources such as songs, video, etc. from a central computer known as Server.



Computer Network Types:
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________


A computer network is a group of computers linked to each other that enables the computer to communicate with another computer and share their resources, data, and applications.


Types of the computer network 

i)LAN local area network.

ii)PAN personal area network.

iii) MAN metropolitan area network.

iv) WAN wide area network.


PAN :

personal Area Network is a network arranged within an individual person, typically within a range of 10 meters.

...Personal computer devices that are used to develop the personal area network are the laptop, mobile phones, media player and play stations.



LAN :

Local Area Network is a group of computers connected to each other in a small area such as building, office.



...It is less costly as it is built with inexpensive hardware such as hubs, network adapters, and ethernet cables.

...The data is transferred at an extremely faster rate in Local Area Network.

...Local Area Network provides higher security.





MAN :

A metropolitan area network is a network that covers a larger geographic area by interconnecting a different LAN to form a larger network.

...in MAN, various LANs are connected to each other.


MAN is used in communication between the banks in a city.
It can be used in an Airline Reservation.
It can be used in a college within a city.
It can also be used for communication in the military.


WAN :

A Wide Area Network is a network that extends over a large geographical area such as states or countries.


...The internet is one of the biggest WAN in the world.


....



Different Types Of The Protocols:

____________________________________________________________________________________________________________

protocol : It is a "set of rules" which are used in digital communication to connect network devices and exchange information between them.

...> set of rules that are establisheed to process.



Types of protocol:
1)TCP/IP
2)HTTP (hyper text transfer protocol)
3)SMTP (simple mail transfer protocol)

..> it is used to transfer the emails from one user to another 
...> while working on this protocol we need to at both ends sender and recevier need to have the internet.


4)POP(post office protocol) 

..> it is also  used to transfer the emails from one user to another.but
...> while working on this protocol we need not to have the internet at the receiver end.



5)FTP (file transfer protocol)
6)ARP( address resolution protocol) 
7)IMAP
8)UDP (User datagram protol)
9)PPP
10)DHCP (dynamic host configuration protocol)
11)DNS( domain name system protocol) 



EVERY host(computer) need four items for the internet conncetivity

   ...Ip address: hosts identity on the internet
   ...subnet mask: size of the host's network 
 
 With the above two communicate with devices which are in the local area network/with in the network size only , but not outside the network.

   ...Default Gateway: router's ip address for connecting to the outside network/internet
   ...DNS Server Ip's: for connecting to the other outside webs.












12)
13)SLIP (Serial Line Internal Protocol)
14) 


note: IP v4 : the complete routing of the data packet from source to the destination is done by the IP v4.



Address resolution protocol:

..>This protocol is used for the communication.

..> In the est of comminication between two computers we need the IP  adddress , MAC address, here IP Address gives the which network in need to go , AND MAC addres gives to which system to conect in that network . THis ARP has the table with all the mac address.

...> By this protocol only the proper IP add is "mapped" to the proper MAC addre.


EX: By this protocol only our dell laptop can talk to the vivo phone 



ICMP: internet control message protocol 

..> by using this protocol n/w devices will send the error messages, when ever any error is occured between the devices while transfering the data.  



TCP tRansmission control protocol:

..> this is responsible  transfering the data packets from source to destination with the combination of the IP 
 
..> By using the acknowledgement method it will check the errors.If error occurs then it will re-transmit the data.

..> It is also called the connection oriented protocol.


UDP: User data gram protocol:

...> This is a connectionless protocol.

..> This protocol just used to send the data from source to destination that-it's..

it's nothing to do with 
...>No reliability , NO error checking , NO re-transmission of data packet.



FTP : File Tranfer Protocol:

..>This protocol is used to transfer the files, between the two systems.Like a client and server on a computer network.

..> FTP is built on a client-server model .

..> protocols : These are set rules used the by the computers to communicate.

..> The default FTP Port number is 21.

..> To show the demo of this protocol we need the two linux systems.


++++++++++                           ++++++++++ 
         +                           + Ser    +
client-A +   ......FTP...........>>  + ver-B  +
++++++++++                           ++++++++++
                                      FTPD =21

NOTE: Here a client-A wants to send the file to the server-B by using the FTP Protocol, if the  receiving server-B  does not have,  running any kind of the listeing service to receive  that FTP Protocol  the it will be rejected.
..> so for this purpose we need to have ftpd daemon on the receiving server.



